text: Altissimo (Italian, 'very high', feminine form altissima) is the uppermost register on woodwind instruments. Altissimo may also refer to: * Altissimo (album), by Gary Bartz, Lee Konitz, Jackie McLean and Charlie Mariano, 1973 * Altissimo, Veneto, a place in Italy * Monte Altissimo, a mountain in the Bergamasque Prealps, Italy *Renato Altissimo (1940–2015), an Italian politician *Cristofano dell'Altissimo (c. 1525–1605), an Italian painter ==See also== * *
